        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/metalperformanceshaders/mpsunaryimagekernel",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " defines shared behavior for most image processing kernels (filters) such as edging modes, clipping, and tiling support for image operations that consumes a single source textures. It is not meant to be used directly, but provides API abstraction and in some cases may allow some level of polymorphic manipulation of image kernel objects.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
